How can I use an adjective to modify "peoples" in this sentence: 
<?php
$peoples = ["African", "Asian", "European", "Indigenous", "Latino", "Middle Eastern"];
shuffle($peoples);
$selected = array_slice($peoples, 0, 3);
echo "There are many diverse " . implode(", ", $selected) . " peoples across the world with varying cultural traditions. How do these differences impact their celebrations?";
?>
I want to make the sentence more specific by randomly selecting and including three adjectives to describe "peoples". Can you help me modify the PHP code accordingly?

Certainly! You can modify the PHP script to include a list of adjectives and then randomly select and pair them with the selected peoples. Here’s how you can do it:

```php
<?php
$peoples = ["African", "Asian", "European", "Indigenous", "Latino", "Middle Eastern"];
$adjectives = ["vibrant", "ancient", "rich", "colorful", "dynamic", "unique"];
shuffle($peoples);
shuffle($adjectives);

// Select three random peoples
$selectedPeoples = array_slice($peoples, 0, 3);
// Select three random adjectives
$selectedAdjectives = array_slice($adjectives, 0, 3);

// Combine them into a descriptive phrase
$descriptivePhrases = [];
for ($i = 0; $i < count($selectedPeoples); $i++) {
    $descriptivePhrases[] = $selectedAdjectives[$i] . " " . $selectedPeoples[$i];
}

echo "There are many diverse " . implode(", ", $descriptivePhrases) . " peoples across the world with varying cultural traditions. How do these differences impact their celebrations?";
?>
```

This code now randomly selects three adjectives and pairs them with the selected peoples to create a more detailed sentence. The adjectives and peoples are shuffled separately to ensure randomness. The `implode` function then joins these descriptive phrases into a single string for output.
